rian Turnebus, who knew all things, what he thought of that book; who made answer, “That he thought it was some abstract drawn from St. Thomas d’Aquin; for that, in truth, his mind, so full of infinite erudition and admirable subtlety, was alone capable of such thoughts.</p><p>t///</p><p>///h</p><p>[_L]St.Thomas d’Aquin.</p><p>h///</p><p><br></p>","custparents":[{"idx":"MY566de29f-fd17-47e2-a9b0-948c613ebecd"}]},{"idx":"9ed8fba5-1e77-4e8d-b6d8-45f4c05ddd46","name":"A man of great judgement","NodeDescription":"///t\r\n” Be this as it may, whoever was the author and inventor (and ‘tis not reasonable, without greater certainty, to deprive Sebond of that title), he was a man of great judgment and most admirable parts.t///\r\n///h\r\nh///","custparents":[{"idx":"MY566de29f-fd17-47e2-a9b0-948c613ebecd"}]}]},{"idx":"MY5b095b6d-1800-4c65-871d-b10a46b2c15d","name":"His views get reprehended","custparents":[{},{"idx":"MY6fd2031d-f027-428a-9b2f-b2f4970bacb2"}],"children":[{"idx":"b4c8c268-d9c9-4a9a-8fed-e5e939dc33a0","name":"Reposing reasoning upon belief","children":[{"idx":"9560b8e6-a19b-4a86-b1b2-f0c8613dbd71","name":"Was blamed for his statement that people believe but not reason","NodeDescription":"<p>///t The first thing they reprehend in his work is “That Christians are to blame to <span style=\"background-color: rgb(153, 51, 255);\">repose their belief upon human reason</span>, which is only conceived by faith and the particular inspiration of divine grace.t/// ///h h///</p>"},{"idx":"81c82f61-54d4-4489-9eeb-90935aecf616","name":"Need to endeavor to","NodeDescription":"<p>///t ” In which objection there appears to be something of zeal to piety, and therefore we are to endeavour to satisfy those who put it forth with the greater mildness and respect.</p><p>t/// ///h h///</p>"},{"idx":"698f43bd-7fab-4667-b622-7d5559585566","name":"A more divine man would help","NodeDescription":"///t\r\n This were a task more proper for a man well read in divinity than for me, who know n