re, dost thy light display.t///\r\n///h\r\nh///"}]},{"idx":"2fdc09c3-8c4c-48f8-9430-7d782d58684e","name":"paragraph347","children":[{"idx":"4995587b-2850-4cf6-aa02-c85fd65620ac","name":"347.0","NodeDescription":"///t\r\n  Pallada Cecropid, Minola Creta Dianam,\r\n  Vulcanum tellus Hypsipylea colit,\r\n  Junonem Sparte, Pelopeladesque Mycen;\r\n  Pinigerum Fauni Mnalis ora caput;\r\n  Mars Latio venerandus.t///\r\n///h\r\nh///"}]},{"idx":"819a9209-5814-4460-a1fb-2defc6401d38","name":"paragraph348","children":[{"idx":"a233ea77-dc19-49ba-b3cb-e20a65d07ba3","name":"348.0","NodeDescription":"///t\r\n  “Th’ Athenians Pallas, Cynthia Crete adore,\r\n  Vulcan is worshipped on the Lemnian shore.t///\r\n///h\r\nh///"},{"idx":"133b915c-60ce-42ac-979c-32ae989c95a2","name":"348.1","NodeDescription":"///t\r\n\r\n  Proud Juno’s altars are by Spartans fed,\r\n  Th’ Arcadians worship Faunus, and ‘tis said\r\n  To Mars, by Italy, is homage paid.t///\r\n///h\r\nh///"}]}]},{"name":"tmp.46","children":[{"idx":"d6188318-2323-4eae-b1c7-01dc648540dc","name":"paragraph350","children":[{"idx":"7aabf745-47db-4575-b2e7-54c93fa6d8c4","name":"350.0","NodeDescription":"///t\r\nHic illius arma, Hic currus fuit.t///\r\n///h\r\nh///"}]},{"idx":"91761226-4e2e-407c-9b4d-1f2e65d98073","name":"paragraph351","children":[{"idx":"5eb0edf3-1ab1-4ecc-b05e-4dc5119f9f06","name":"351.0","NodeDescription":"///t\r\nJunctaque sunt magno templa nepotis avo.t///\r\n///h\r\nh///"}]},{"idx":"985e6454-53a7-4038-86ed-c06721fd4c39","name":"paragraph352","children":[{"idx":"0c50d40f-6ea0-462b-afda-c92527b5fc0d","name":"352.0","NodeDescription":"///t\r\n“And temples to the nephew joined are,\r\nTo those were reared to the great-grandfather.t///\r\n///h\r\nh///"}]},{"idx":"068d89e0-06c5-42ac-93ba-32a10403dbc2","name":"paragraph353","children":[{"idx":"ed2940a0-a882-4b6a-82aa-dac39b5c3ea5","name":"353.0","NodeDescription":"///t\r\nIn here are some so wretched and mean (for the number amounts to six and thirty thousand) that 